on laws can be expressed in closed-form relationships. This study reformulates the ER\u003dEPR conjecture entirely within QA, linking wormhole geometry and quantum entanglement through tuple symmetry and harmonic conservation.\n\n---\n\n## **2. Key Findings \u0026 Validations**\n\n### **2.1 Theoretical Insights**\n\n* ER bridges correspond to **elliptic extensions** of the tuple family ((J,X,K)).\n* EPR pairs correspond to **entangled ends** of ((b,e,d,a)).\n* The connecting invariant is (X \u003d e·d): **the half-distance between foci**—identical in both geometric and entanglement contexts.\n* Conservation of information arises from the tuple symmetry:\n  [\n  J + K \u003d 2D, \\quad W \u003d X + K.\n  ]\n  Equality ((W \u003d 2D)) only occurs when (b \u003d e), defining the *Central Pipe*.\n\n### **2.2 Computational Verification**\n\n| Tuple     | (J) | (K) | (X) | (D) | (J+K) | (W) | Symmetry               |\n| :-------- | :-- | :-- | :-- | :-- | :---- | :-- | :--------------------- |\n| (2,2,4,6) | 8   | 24  | 8   | 16  | 32    | 32  | **b\u003de (Central Pipe)** |\n| (1,2,3,5) | 3   | 15  | 6   | 9   | 18    | 21  | Asymmetric             |\n\nThese results confirm that (J+K\u003d2D) universally holds, but (W\u003d2D) holds **only** under the Central Pipe condition, demonstrating the symmetry required for firewall-free information flow.\n\n---\n\n## **3. Mathematical Formulations**\n\nAll QA operations stem from the canonical tuple ((b,e,d,a)) and its derived variables:\n\n[\n\\begin{align}\nb \u0026\u003d \\text{base leg}, \u0026 e \u0026\u003d \\text{variation or inner leg}, \\\nd \u0026\u003d b+e, \u0026 a \u0026\u003d e+d \u003d b+2e, \\\nB \u0026\u003d b^2, \u0026 E \u0026\u003d e^2, \\\nD \u0026\u003d d^2, \u0026 A \u0026\u003d a^2.\n\\end{align}\n]\n\n**Derived QA quantities:**\n\n[\n\\begin{align}\nX \u0026\u003d e·d \\quad \u0026\\text{(Half-distance between foci)}, \\\nC \u0026\u003d 2e·d \\quad \u0026\\text{(Full distance between foci)}, \\\nF \u0026